$interpreted: Maeok: Chieftain... They both have Holy Talismans. What should we do?
Tapir Chieftain: This... Never before, happened.
Tapir Chieftain: Two people, two talismans, must have reason. Maybe, Udumbara's, will.
Maeok: You mean... they can both participate in the finals?
Shun: That's insane! The tournament isn't some children's game!
Turtle Chieftain: That's right! Changing the rules like this makes a mockery of everything we stand for!
Maeok: Quiet, everyone. Please...
Bull Chieftain: Quiet my butt! Quit acting all high and mighty after what's happened with your daughter!
Toyokuni: Enough! Soohyeon has nothing to do with this, what's the point of bringing her up!?
Panther Chieftain: That wasn't his point...
Toyokuni: And what was his point!? Have you all forgotten that Maeok is still our arbiter? Where is your respect!?
Qing-Feng: Toyokuni is right, and yet... It is understandable that our chieftains have their misgivings, even if the Tapir Chieftain's word is sagely.
Toyokuni: And why have misgivings!? The Tapir Chieftain comes appointed by the Keeper of the Udumbara. How could any of us know better than she!?
Qing-Feng: Yes, tradition begets tradition, rules beget rules, and yet... These rules are made in service of fairness and consistency.
Qing-Feng: And now, letting these criminals participate in the games flies directly in the face of all fairness. Who does this decision serve!?
Wolf Chieftain: Qing-Feng is right! If this is allowed, then in the future anyone could just jump out from the shadows and join the games at the last minute!
Tapir Chieftain: Everyone, doubt, Udumbara? Doubt, Holy Dragon?
Qing-Feng: We do not doubt such deities. This is simply a complicated matter that demands careful decisionmaking...
Tapir Chieftain: East, all things, no matter, one petal, blade of grass, all connected, Holy Dragon. By extension, arbiter.
Tapir Chieftain: Your words, supersede, Holy Dragon? Arbiter?
Qing-Feng: Ah... I...
Maeok: As the Tapir Chieftain said, this is the Holy Dragon's will. Please, trust that the Holy Dragon will lead us in the right direction.
Qing-Feng: I would never go against the Holy Dragon's will, and yet... The Capybara Tribe is not allowed to compete. Would the Holy Dragon accept such a contestant?
Toyokuni: It is the Holy Dragon's will.
Toyokuni: And if they're not worthy, then the Holy Dragon will not let them pass the following trials.
Qing-Feng: ...Then, do the other two contestants accept this newcomer?
Tindoiimu: I don't care, I never expected any of this to be fair in the first place.
Pang: I... do not object.
Maeok: Both parties do not object, so it is settled.
Qing-Feng: Hmph... Don't forget this moment if things don't go your way.
Maeok: ......
Yao: Can we just get this over with now?
Tapir Chieftain: ...Three contestants, please enter.
Pang: Yao...
Tindoiimu: Is this the Dream Flower?
Tapir Chieftain: Yes.
Pang: What is this?
Pang: ...It has an odd smell.
Tapir Chieftain: This, Dream Broth, from, Udumbara sap...
Tapir Chieftain: Drink deep, sleep, see, Keeper of the Udumbara.
Tindoiimu: Alright, let's finally get a good look at this Keeper.
Tindoiimu: Are we in a dream? Feels a lot like reality...
???: Maybe that is because dreams are a sort of reality.
Tindoiimu: Who are you?
???: Who am I? That is a difficult question to answer.
Tindoiimu: ...Are you the Keeper of the Udumbara?
???: Or am I not?
Tindoiimu: (Is this some kind of test...?)
???: Are you thinking?
???: Thinking is of no use here.
???: Like a dream, you know not when it begins. And whether what appears in front of you---
???: Is truly what you see.
Tindoiimu: ...Jiyanama!?
Pang: But, how!?
Tindoiimu: Impossible... Jiyanama is dead...
Tindoiimu: Jiya... nama?
???: She lives in your heart.
Tindoiimu: It's you!?

???: A day's thoughts turn to a midnight's dream,
A heart's desire to what the heart may be.
???: Is the you, here and now, ready to face the truth?
Tindoiimu: The truth...
???: Answer me---
???: Where is your home?
Tindoiimu: My home...
Tindoiimu: My home is with the Insect Tribe.
???: What is your heart's desire?
Tindoiimu: I only have one desire. To cut down the Udumbara, to avenge my tribe.
Tindoiimu: What's going on...!?
???: A strong answer...
???: And yet the stronger the answer, the deeper the fear. I hear... I hear your fear, your guilt...
Tindoiimu: Fear? Guilt? What are you talking about!?
Tindoiimu: Sooh... yeon!?
???: Did you see it? Hear it?
Soohyeon: You're a good person... I know you are...
Tindoiimu: No, you're not the real Soohyeon... you're not her...
Soohyeon: Why... become... just like them...?
Tindoiimu: You're not...
Tindoiimu: Stay away from me!
Tindoiimu: What do you want from me!? You want to torture me!?
???: No one is torturing you but yourself.
Tindoiimu: Enough! I've had enough of this!
???: Afraid... of yourself... running away... from yourself...
Tindoiimu: There's more!?
Pang: Relax, I am not a dream.
Tindoiimu: ...You're that tiger...
Tindoiimu: What are you doing here?
Pang: I am not sure myself. This may be a part of the trials.
Tindoiimu: Are we in the same dream? Are our dreams... connected?
Pang: I do not know.
???: The road... ahead...
Tindoiimu: It's that voice.
Tindoiimu: You want us to follow the light?
Tindoiimu: Is something wrong?
Pang: ...If we're here together as part of the trial, then... where is Yao?
